title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin April 1963
summary: Bulletin announcing events including a conference on Computers in Design, a symposium on Computer Graphics, and an international exhibition in Zagreb. Includes information on EVENT ONE, membership, and publications.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin June 1963
summary: Bulletin covering public meetings such as 'How to Write a Computer Dance' and exhibitions like INNC 70. Highlights include membership details, a non-numerical programming workshop, and calls for art contest submissions.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin August 1963
summary: This bulletin discusses public meetings, DataFair 69, and critiques on computer art in exhibitions like 'SOFTWARE' at the Jewish Museum. Includes membership details, publications, and a call for submissions to upcoming exhibitions.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin September 1963
summary: Includes announcements of society meetings, review of MUSIC V, and updates on Datafair 69. Details collaboration initiatives and mentions developments in electronic music.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin November 1969
summary: The bulletin details society objectives, membership benefits, upcoming exhibitions like 'On the Eve of Tomorrow' in Hannover, and contributions from members. Includes A. Michael Noll's writings on computer art.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin February 1970
summary: Focus on computer music and notable composers such as David Lewin, Jim Tenney, and Jean-Claude Risset. Also covers international exhibitions and activities in the UK and abroad.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin March 1970
summary: Discusses ART1 program and design techniques, along with international exhibitions and artist opportunities. Reflects on future developments in computer art.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin May 1970
summary: Announcements of meetings, traveling exhibitions, and programming courses. Discusses international computer art activities and contributions to Computer Graphics 70.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin July 1970
summary: Highlights include computer-designed stamps, the Blue Cube project, and updates from CASH (Computer Arts Society Holland). Includes reports from international computer art activities.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin September 1970
summary: Details society activities, upcoming exhibitions, and contributions to the field. Includes updates from international groups and reports on computer art education initiatives.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin November 1970
summary: Announces new collaborations, exhibitions, and the publication of articles on computer aesthetics. Includes updates on software developments and international computer art news.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin January 1971
summary: Focuses on computer graphics research, exhibitions in the UK and USA, and educational initiatives for artists exploring algorithmic processes.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin March 1971
summary: Highlights conferences on computer art, including papers on generative aesthetics and digital sound. Mentions international collaborations and new publications.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin May 1971
summary: Reports on member exhibitions, algorithmic design projects, and educational workshops for computer-aided art. Notes the increasing interest in digital image processing.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin July 1971
summary: Discusses advancements in computer animation and its application in art. Includes reviews of recent exhibitions and announcements for upcoming events.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin September 1971
summary: Explores algorithmic sculpture and digital sound synthesis. Highlights international partnerships and contributions from leading figures in computer arts.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin November 1971
summary: Covers developments in interactive installations and generative systems. Features articles on cybernetic art and computer-assisted choreography.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin January 1972
summary: Highlights recent publications on computer aesthetics and theoretical frameworks for algorithmic art. Notes conferences and society initiatives.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin March 1972
summary: Reports on collaborations between artists and technologists. Includes updates on software tools for creative work and educational workshops.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin May 1972
summary: Covers algorithmic drawing systems and interactive installations. Highlights international exhibitions and member contributions to journals.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin July 1972
summary: Details new techniques in digital printmaking and discusses the integration of computer technologies in traditional art forms. Includes reviews of major exhibitions.

title: Computer Arts Society Bulletin September 1972
summary: Announces upcoming conferences and calls for papers on computer aesthetics. Discusses cybernetic art projects and international collaborations.
